race.comment: THE WHEELBARROW (11) overcame a poor start to win with plenty in hand last start over 1650m at this track. Taking on a better race today but he is lightly raced and heading the right way. Big chance to go back-to-back. LARIDAE (9) settled a long way back after a slow start then rallied late to get up for fourth last time out over 1350m here. That followed a five-week let-up so he definitely strips fitter and the step up to a mile is another tick. Poses a genuine threat. HEADHUNTER (1) opened this campaign with a couple of wins then was just fair through the line when midfield in a BM70 over the mile at Eagle Farm most recently. The 3kg claim is a smart move so a return to form looks on the cards. ITALIAN DANCER (5) led from the outset and toyed with his Rockhampton rivals over 1500m last start. Going too well to dismiss. PELE PRINCESS (12) is racing well and gets Vlad Duric back in the saddle today - he has won two from two on the mare.
